There were somethings that became clearer to me


-- State Notifier is a flutter class, it works directly from Flutter and helps us to listen to any changes in the state of our widgets. 

-- Using the Consumer Widget which is a descendant of the ConsumerWidget Widget which in turn is also from ConsumerStatefulWidget Widget, 
-- and then eventually extends Stateful widget, we can listen to changes in our application without rebuilding the entire application
-- overall avoid listening to a provider in the build process.

